      • test_serializationSize

        public void test_serializationSize()
        Writes the serialized size of an instance on stdout. It is an amazing 61 bytes. You can serialize just the SPOKeyOrder.index() byte value for an amazing 60 byte savings per instance.

      • test_keyOrder_triples

        public void test_keyOrder_triples()
        Unit tests verifies all of the triple key encoding orders. It encodes a known key in each order in turn and verifies by decoding using the SPO key order and checking against the expected permutation of the (s,p,o) values.

      • test_keyOrder_quads

        public void test_keyOrder_quads()
        Unit tests verifies all of the quad key encoding orders. It encodes a known key in each order in turn and verifies by decoding using the SPOC key order and checking against the expected permutation of the (s,p,o,c) values.
